sentences: Harold Hastings (19 December 1916 – 30 May 1973) was an American composer and conductor.
In 1950, he composed the music for the Broadway revue Tickets, Please!.
From 1950 to 1973, he worked as musical director or arranger for twenty-five Broadway musicals, several of which became renowned classics of Broadway.
In 1973, he died of an apparent heart attack at his home in Larchmont, New York.
A Funny Thing Happened on the Way to the Forum (1962)
